passages.text: Lao Feng Xiang's (LFX) 2Q25 NI beat RMB607m, up \(1\%\) yoy and \(25\% /11\%\) higher than GSe/VA consensus, mainly due to higher government subsidy of RMB350m while OP missed at RMB702m, down \(35\%\) yoy and \(21\% /19\%\) lower than GSe/VA consensus driven by higher sales taxes and lower GPM partially offset by better sales. In addition, we note the company turned from 297 net closures in 1Q25 to 9 net opening in 2Q25. The company announced an interim dividend of RMB0.33 per share, implying \(14\%\) dividend payout ratio, vs. GSe of RMB1.91 or \(45\%\) payout for full year 2025. We think the 2Q better sales but lower GPM is likely indicative of the company's strategies to increase franchises' incentives/rebates to boost sell- in inventories.
We are Neutral rated on LFX.

Sales increased by \(32\%\) yoy in 2Q25 to RMB15.8bn, \(8\%\) higher than GSe.
Store network: In 2Q25, the company net opened 8 stores in ML China, all are franchise store and 1 net openings of direct store in overseas market. In total, LFX net closed 288 stores in 1H25.
Gross margin came in 2.4ppt lower yoy at \(8.3\%\) in 2Q25, 0.2ppt lower than GSe of \(8.5\%\) .
Selling expenses decreased \(4\%\) yoy in 2Q25 to RMB208m, \(9\%\) above GSe, while selling expenses sales ratio was down 0.2ppt yoy and in line with GSe at \(1.3\%\) .
Admin expenses came down \(31\%\) yoy in 2Q25 to RMB108m, \(24\%\) above GSe, with \(1\%\) sales ratio down 0.4ppt yoy to \(0.7\%\) and 0.1ppt above GSe.
Operating profit decreased by \(37\%\) yoy in 2Q25 to RMB702m, \(21\%\) lower than GSe mainly due to lower GPM, higher sales tax and add- on driven by higher stamp

Non- operating gain/(losses): Non- operating gain recorded RMB298m vs. GSe of RMB23m mainly due to higher government subsidy at c.RMB350m.
Effective tax rate: \(24\%\) , declined 3.4ppt and came in 1.2ppt below GSe.

NI attributed to equity shareholders: NI increased by \(1\%\) yoy in 2Q25 to RMB607m, \(25\%\) above GSe due to higher sales and higher non- op gain, partially offset by higher sales tax and add- on. NPM recorded \(3.8\%\) , down 0.4ppt, yet higher than GSe at \(3.3\%\) .
Dividend: The company announced an interim dividend of RMB0.33 per share, implying \(14\%\) dividend ratio, vs. GSe at RMB1.91 or \(45\%\) payout for full year 2025.

We derive our \(12m\) TP of RMB51 based on \(12x\) 2025E target PE, in line with base target PE and also in line with LFX's 1std below historical average PE. Key risks: 1) Faster/slower gold sentiment recovery; 2) Faster/slower store expansion; 3) Margin expansion/contraction higher than expected on gold price volatility.

The Goldman Sachs Factor Profile provides investment context for a stock by comparing key attributes to the market (i.e. our universe of rated stocks) and its sector peers. The four key attributes depicted are: Growth, Financial Returns, Multiple (e.g. valuation) and Integrated (a composite of Growth, Financial Returns and Multiple). Growth, Financial Returns and Multiple are calculated by using normalized ranks for specific metrics for each stock. The normalized ranks for the metrics are then averaged and converted into percentiles for the relevant attribute. The precise calculation of each metric may vary depending on the fiscal year, industry and region, but the standard approach is as follows:

Growth is based on a stock's forward- looking sales growth, EBITDA growth and EPS growth (for financial stocks, only EPS and sales growth), with a higher percentile indicating a higher growth company. Financial Returns is based on a stock's forward- looking ROE, ROCE and CROCI (for financial stocks, only ROE), with a higher percentile indicating a company with higher financial returns. Multiple is based on a stock's forward- looking P/E, P/B, price/dividend (P/D), EV/EBITDA, EV/FCF and EV/Debt Adjusted Cash Flow (DACF) (for financial stocks, only P/E, P/B and P/D), with a higher percentile indicating a stock trading at a higher multiple. The Integrated percentile is calculated as the average of the Growth percentile, Financial Returns percentile and (100% - Multiple percentile).

Financial Returns and Multiple use the Goldman Sachs analyst forecasts at the fiscal year- end at least three quarters in the future. Growth uses inputs for the fiscal year at least seven quarters in the future compared with the year at least three quarters in the future (on a per- share basis for all metrics).
For a more detailed description of how we calculate the GS Factor Profile, please contact your GS representative.
